qas.question: What does .org on a URL mean?

answers.text: organizations that didn't fit anywhere else

qas.question: Are only NPOs allowed to use .org?

answers.text: not designated specifically for charitable organizations or any specific organizational or tax-law status

qas.question: What is included in the list of organizations allowed to use .org?

answers.text: encompasses anything that is not classifiable as another category

qas.question: Is there an agency that decides if someone is using the domain designation incorrectly?

answers.text: Currently, no restrictions are enforced on registration of .com or .org

qas.question: What new domain designation should a museum use?
What does tld in a URL mean?
What group is .org designated specifically for?

plausible_answers.text: non-commercial organizations if they are not governmental, educational, or one of the other types

qas.question: What other groups fit into the domain tld?
What restrictions are there enforced on tld?
What can governments register by in their country?
